commit_list.message:
Offloading most of the delayed logic into the attachment itself and a queue on the model
* Using Paperclip native post_processing = false to halt post processing on assignment
* queuing all enqueueing similar to how writes are enqueued by papaerclip
* "flushing" the enqueueing after_save (or after_commit if supported)
* Using paperclip's attachment_definitions to store configuration (delayed, priority)
* Posibility to create more processors
